= Socialist Congress

Talks between the NCWPP and NCSDP over the years have been strained, to say the least. Hushed talks of a united socialist front have been brewing for years among the party's [? if cp_radicalization > 5: radicals ?][? if cp_radicalization < 6: moderates ?], but now those plans are finally coming to fruition.

The [? if cp_radicalization > 5: moderates ?][? if cp_radicalization < 6: radicals ?] of the [? if cp_radicalization > 5: NCSDP ?][? if cp_radicalization < 6: NCWPP ?] are the only stumbling block of this merger. Will they prove to be too problematic?

- @usp_formed: The party votes...

