The momentum towards socialist unity has proven too great for the few holdouts within the [? if cp_radicalization > 5: NCSDP ?][? if cp_radicalization < 6: NCWPP ?]'s [? if cp_radicalization > 5: moderates ?][? if cp_radicalization < 6: radicals ?]. The parties have officially voted to approve the merger, as the United Socialist Party (USP) comes to fruition.
